      "body" : "The <code>.</code> character in regex means any character other than new line. <a href=\"http://www.tutorialspoint.com/java/java_regular_expressions.htm\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">tutorialspoint.com/java/java_regular_expressions.htm</a> In this case, however, they wanted the actual character <code>.</code>. The two backslashes indicate that you are referring to <code>.</code>. The backslash is an escape character."
